Cephaloleia congener Baly 1885 : 12. Blackwelder 1946 : 718 (catalog); Papp 1953 : 15 (catalog); Uhmann 1957a : 17 (catalog); Wilcox 1983 : 136 (catalog); Staines 1996 : 22 (Central America species), 2004 : 312 (host plants), 2011 : 48 (faunal list); Maes 1999 : 1016 (faunal list); Staines and Staines 1999 : 523 (Baly species list); McKenna and Farrell 2005 : 119 (phylogeny), 2006 : 10949 (phylogeny);
Garcia-Robledo et al. 2013a
: 3 (biology), 2013b : 193 (biology).

Adults have been collected from Heliconia latispatha Bentham and Heliconia tortuosa Griggs ( Heliconiaceae ) ( Staines 1996 ); Heliconia imbricata Baker, Heliconia irrasa R. R. Sm., Heliconia mathiasiae G. S. Daniels and F. G. Stiles, Heliconia psittacorum Sw., Heliconia pogonantha Cufod., Heliconia sarapiquensis G. S. Daniels and F. G. Stiles, Heliconia wagneriana Peterson, Calathea crotalifera S. Watson, Cephaloleia inocephala Juntze, Ischnosiphon inflatus L. Andersson ( Marantaceae ), Musa velutina H. Wendl. and Drude ( Musaceae ) (
Garcia-Robledo et al. 2013a
).
